says, what is th=\r\ne \ndifference between a gyani and a vigyani? A gyani experiences the state =\r\nof \nNirvikalpa and realizes &quot;All is Brahman&quot;. But it is one thing to realiz=\r\ne &quot;all is \nbrahman&quot;, it is another thing to acquire some of the shaktis of =\r\nBrahman. \n\n=C2=A0 \nF or example, consider a glass of water and an ocean. Bo=\r\nth of them have the same \nchemical compostion (H2O). Realizing this is real=\r\nizing &quot;all is Brahman&quot;. But an \nocean can sustain and create a Tsunami, a g=\r\nlass of water cannot, even if it \nwants to. Of course it may often never ha=\r\nve a desire to do so in the first \nplace! However that is the difference, t=\r\nechnically, between a gyani and a \nvi-gyani. And the whole process of a Sid=\r\ndha and higher starts ONLY AFTER someone \nis able to bring the Kundalini ba=\r\nck from Sahashra chakra to the lower chakras \nagain. Needless to say, for m=\r\nost of us ordinary people, even getting a Kundalini \nto awaken is a big dea=\r\nl, taking it to Shahashrar is already too hi fi and may \ntake lifetimes, br=\r\ninging is back is impossible/unthinkable totally. \n\n=C2=A0 \nWhat happens wh=\r\nen a person becomes a Siddha by the parameter described above? It \nis impos=\r\nsible to imagine. He/she operates from a plane of reference so different \nt=\r\nhat ordinary folks just cannot fathom. Infact, most of us can&#39;t even fathom=\r\n \nwhat samadhi feels like until experienced, what to speak of siddha-hood. =\r\n\n\n=C2=A0 \n__________________________________________ \n=C2=A0 \nA Trilanga Sw=\r\nami did tri-khanda yogas, cuts his limbs, puts them into fire and \neventual=\r\nly the limbs regenerate. Even Sai Baba did a similar thing. Is this a \nsidd=\r\nhi (miraculous ability) or a sadhana? To us average folks, anything out of =\r\n\nthe ordinary seems miraculous. The internet itself would appear \nsupernatu=\r\nral/miraculous a few centuries ago! \n\n=C2=A0 \nTherefore, one who reaches a =\r\nstate of Siddha-hood, will automatically produce \nexternal effects which ap=\r\npear miraculous to ordinary people. Not like he/she is \nspecifically trying=\r\n for it, but it is a byproduct of a totally different \ninternal reference f=\r\nrame. Hence the crucial difference between a &quot;gyani&quot; and a \n&quot;vigyani&quot;. \n\n=\r\n=C2=A0 \nTo give an example from physics, if you could move at speeds close =\r\nto that of \nlight, you will see things elongating, time becoming slower, yo=\r\nu will age less, \netc etc. If you could move at speeds higher than that of =\r\nlight, you will observe \neffects of an action even before the action happen=\r\ns.=C2=A0 A supremely altered \nreference frame creates external effects whic=\r\nh are extraordinary and appear \nmiraculous to observers who are in a differ=\r\nent reference frame. This is the \nreality of the world. No amount of philos=\r\nophy can change this. \n\n=C2=A0 \n___________________________________________=\r\n_____________ \n=C2=A0 \nEvery spiritual book has a point of view and an audi=\r\nence. Same with Aghora. One \nmay like it or one may not like it. But there =\r\nis zero scope of saying \nVimalananda knew something else and book creates a=\r\n different impression etc etc. \nNothing of that sort. The chapter on Immort=\r\nals in book 2 is very, very clear and \nvery direct. It is not possible to i=\r\nnterpret it any other way. \n\n=C2=A0 \nOur scriptures have plenty of stories =\r\nof miraculous things done by and \nassociated with Rishis. Did they have a d=\r\nesire from past lives? Which past life, \nwhen Rishis are eternal? The desir=\r\ne from past-life can explain why a sadhaka who \nhas not yet experienced sta=\r\nte of Brahman (nirvikalpa), striving for and \nattaining xyz supernatural ab=\r\nility, but it cannot explain the external, \nmiraculous occurances which acc=\r\nompany a being who has attain siddha-hood or \nbeyond (Rishis). To me, it is=\r\n a natural byproduct of their vastly different \ninternal state of being. No=\r\nt something they may have strived for, but something \nthat accompanies and =\r\nmanifests externally corresponding to their internal \nmastery over the elem=\r\nents. \n\n=C2=A0 \n-Regards \n=C2=A0Rajarshi \n=C2=A0 \nBazeecha-e-atfal hain dun=\r\niya mere aage. \nHota hain shab-o-roz tamasha mere aage \n=C2=A0 \nEk khel hai=\r\nn aurang-e-sulemaan mere nazdeek \nEk baat hain ijaz-e-masiah mere aage. \n\n\n=\r\n\n___________________________________\n\nFrom: Narasimha PVR Rao &lt;pvr@charter.=\r\nnet&gt; \nTo: vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com \nSent: Thu, 4 August, 2011 1:13:01 A=\r\nM \nSubject: [vedic-wisdom] One more key point (Re: On Siddhis & Spiritual P=\r\nrogress) \n\n\n=C2=A0 \nNamaste, \n=C2=A0 \nAn interesting point came up in a pri=\r\nvate exchange with a couple of folks and I \nwill write it down for the bene=\r\nfit of others. \n\n=C2=A0 \n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 * \n=C2=A0 \nIt is not like &quot;you get =\r\nso & so siddhi when you reach so & so level&quot;. \n=C2=A0 \nSiddhis come because=\r\n one DESIRED them in this or a PREVIOUS life. When one has \nmade enough pro=\r\ngress, Nature grants one&#39;s desires (or the ability to fulfil a \ngroup of de=\r\nsires) and sees if that tempts one and one stops or one can progress \nfurth=\r\ner. \n\n=C2=A0 \nSo what siddhis one gets or does not get, is a function of (1=\r\n) one&#39;s spiritual \nprogress now AND (2) all of one&#39;s desires until now (in =\r\nthis life AND previous \nlives). At the same level of progress, two people m=\r\nay fare differently in terms \nof what they get, based on what kind of wishe=\r\ns they entertained in the past. \n\n=C2=A0 \nSo siddhis cannot be used to meas=\r\nure one&#39;s progress. You cannot use reverse of \nf(x, y) to gauge x, without =\r\nknowing y. \n\n=C2=A0 \nBest regards, \nNarasimha \n----------------------------=\r\n-------------------