at land in their lap by themselves. Some get distracted from the \njourney=\r\n and pursue the fruits actively. Collecting fruits is neither necessary \nno=\r\nr sufficient for reaching the top. Though having a fruit that is available =\r\n\nonly at a very high altitude shows that one has reached great altitude, it=\r\n \ncannot be used as a measure of one&#39;s progress, for someone may have climb=\r\ned \ngreater heights without collecting that (or any) fruit. \n\n=C2=A0 \nExter=\r\nnal and internal do NOT have a one-to-one correspondence. Just as you \ncann=\r\not tell what is inside a house by looking at it from outside, so cannot you=\r\n \ntell one&#39;s state of mind from looking at one. One&#39;s spiritual maturity an=\r\nd \nattainment is in one&#39;s state of mind. \n\n=C2=A0 \n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 * \n=C2=A0=\r\n \n&gt; If a loved and revered spiritual figure is percieved to be questioned, =\r\n\n&gt; naturally a reaction is expected. I am not surprised. \n=C2=A0 \nWhen you =\r\nsaid a while back, for example, that Vivekananda used to contradict \nhimsel=\r\nf, I agreed. The issue is not just &quot;questioning&quot; a &quot;loved and revered \nspir=\r\nitual figure&quot;. The issue is passing off what I see as needless, unjustified=\r\n \nand baseless judgments, driven by misconceptions and a fascination for th=\r\ne \nexternal. \n\n=C2=A0 \nBest regards, \nNarasimha \n--------------------------=\r\n----------------------------------------- \n=C2=A0 Free Jyotish Software, Fr=\r\nee Jyotish Lessons, Jyotish Writings, \n&quot;Do It Yourself&quot; ritual manuals for =\r\nshort Homam and Pitri Tarpana: \n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 http://www.Ved=\r\nicAstrologer.org \n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 Films that make a difference: ht=\r\ntp://SaraswatiFilms.org \n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 Spirituality: http://grou=\r\n